This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the effects of depth and width on the quality of local minima in deep learning. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks. Additionally, since the paper discusses the effects of depth and width on image classification, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is a subfield of AI. Finally, since the paper discusses the optimization of deep learning models, it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
